</big><br><small>"Tails are not for biting or pulling!"</small></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubroddathep.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brodda Thep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/8/02 3:57:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1013.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Very good guide.  </span><hr size=1> There is one time when the MT can be rampaged.  Course then he isn't really the MT.  A person can take regular attacks and rampage attacks if they are the ONLY person on the hate list.  Thus pulling rampage wyverns is a big PITA.<br>
<br>
The thing with the rampage list that makes it tricky is that when you are pulling to many rampage mobs the puller will get on the rampage list.  The rampage mob is of course usually rooted and the puller will bring the mobs back to camp.  He will then get healed and the healer will get on rampage list.  Then he will step into the AE bard song and the bard song will get added to rampage.  Thus the most common people to be rampaged are bards and clerics.  Of course if the mob isn't rooted the bards and healers still get on rampage cause bard has a song on MT and clerics heal MT before other mellee attack often times.  <br>
<br>
But master the rules above and you will master AL.  AL is the true test of your understanding of rampage.  If you don't understand it, you will die to AL.<br>
<br>
Also I wouldn't try camping out to clear rampage list UNLESS you camp everyone out and at some point NO ONE is on the mob's hate list.  So this is a big waste of time.  Just memwipe or attone a few times while you have rampage tanks tossing range items at the mob.<br>
<br>
Make sure that your rampage tanks know not to die.  This seems like a stupid thing to say, but it is actually up to them to live.  It is a simple thing to just step out of rampage range if they drop too low on hp and wait for the heal to come.  After all, as soon as they step back in, they will be back taking the rampage.  This is especially important if you lose a rampage tank against the AL.  The person that next takes the rampage needs to stay alive long enough to get heals going to him.  That may mean backing out of rampage range until the heals start coming in.<br>
<br>
And monks are the best rampage tanks due to FD and SS and mend.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umianya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mianya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 4:05:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1013.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Arch lich Rhag Zadune</span><hr size=1> I find I can wedge myself quite easily infront of the altar behind him.  Shrunk but not levitated.  Just keep walking backwards into it.<br>
<br>
Occasionally he'll knock me over/behind it, or if he turns around I may get blasted to the door.  But not more than once or twice a fight, and he usually summons be right back.<br>
<br>
We use 1 MT and set up a few RT's.  Don't usually lose MT's but have lost an RT now and then if they decide they want to attack with EB weapons and steal agro...so make sure your RT tanks don't do that...Your RT tank can probably just sit there with attack of.<br>
<br>
If he's got a Tendonslicer, it really does suck heh.<br>
